Step-by-Step Plan
Project Setup

Initialize the React project.
Install necessary dependencies like react-router-dom, tailwindcss, and any other libraries you might need.
Create Components

Registration Page
Login Page
Home Page
Profile Page
Todo List Component
Todo Item Component
Header Component
Footer Component
Protected Route Component
Routing

Set up routing using react-router-dom.
Define routes for Registration, Login, Home, and Profile pages.
Implement Protected Route for Home Page.
State Management

Use useState for managing local state.
Use useEffect for side effects like fetching data from localStorage.
CRUD Operations

Implement functions to add, update, delete, and filter tasks.
Persist data using localStorage.
Authentication

Implement simple authentication flow (register, login, logout).
Protect Home Page with authentication.
Styling

Use Tailwind CSS for styling.
Ensure responsiveness across different screen sizes.
